title: Feature - ragKnowledge enhancements (double byte support, caching, load from directories)
body:
From testing with the current interation of ragKnowledge, encountered the following issues:

- Double byte characters are stripped (e.g., Chinese)
- Knowledge is re-embedded everytime on agent startup
- Have to enumerate each file you want to load as knowledge

So I'm working on enhancing the rag knowledge feature to support the above.   Otherwise it will be very hard to support large sets of knowledge across multiple files and agent startup will be very slow (as re-embedding has to happen every restart)

title: Fix: [plugin-chainbase] Enhance Query Text Extraction and Validation for QUERY_BLOCKCHAIN_DATA Action
body:
Title: Enhance Query Text Extraction and Validation for QUERY_BLOCKCHAIN_DATA Action

**Description**
Currently in `queryData.ts`, we use a simple string slice method to extract query text:

While this approach works, it has several potential issues:
1. Lacks structured validation for extracted text
2. May contain inappropriate or potentially dangerous content  
3. No explicit query format constraints

**Proposed Improvements**
Consider implementing the following optimizations:
1. Define query templates or structured formats
2. Add query text validation rules
3. Implement content filtering mechanisms
4. Consider using regex or more structured parsing approaches

**Implementation Ideas**
1. Create a query template system
2. Add input validation middleware
3. Establish whitelist rules for query text
4. Improve error message accuracy

**Priority**
Medium - Consider implementing in future releases

title: Make ServiceType can be extended without modify package/core
body:
**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**

Currently, when someone want to create a new service, they must add new type as string to enum ServiceType in packages/core/src/types.

**Describe the solution you'd like**

I want to add new service type in my new plugin without modify enum ServiceType in package core. In some case they import packages/cores from node-modules, so they can not edit that enum

**Describe alternatives you've considered**

May be remove that enum, so that getService function in packages/core/src/runtime.ts we can use 
```
getService<T extends Service>(service: string)
```
instead of
```
getService<T extends Service>(service: ServiceType)
```

title: Low performance issues under parallel requests ?
body:
**Describe the bug**

I do a stress testing to `DirectClient`, but low performance. Here's the stress testing report: https://app.artillery.io/share/sh_973944e7b55ad120fef7a5e6c2a71980c176b5ab38b788baa7c3caa2a973f367

You can see almost all the requests timeout.

I guess `generateMessageResponse` will block event loop, so there can only be one concurrent request, but I'm not sure.

https://github.com/elizaOS/eliza/blob/89b6a190449a2e42aaeeef4cb6caec6448442614/packages/core/src/generation.ts#L1270-L1282

**To Reproduce**

Use eliza-starter to start DirectClient, set `OPENAI_API_URL` in `.env`:

```sh
OPENAI_API_URL=http://localhost:5002/v1
```

use [mockai](https://github.com/polly3d/mockai) to setup a mockai server, and set `data/contents.txt` to:
```json
{ "user": "agent1", "text": "Hi", "action": "IGNORE" }
```

start mockai and eliza-starter, then use artillery to run stress testing. Here's artillery config.yml:

```yaml
config:
  target: "http://localhost:3000"
  plugins:
    metrics-by-endpoint:
      useOnlyRequestNames: true
  http:
    timeout: 30
  phases:
    - duration: 120
      arrivalRate: 5
      rampTo: 50
      name: Ramp up load
    - duration: 720
      arrivalRate: 50
      maxVusers: 1000
      name: Sustained load
  variables:
    uuid:
      - 00acb7e1-c8db-0a34-9e4c-b0daadc3775b
      - 0d8ef5f1-d3df-0cbf-8e16-bd5ee0202e7c
      - 83ce34fa-65fa-07fa-926e-73eeb423a589
scenarios:
  - name: "POST /message"
    flow:
      - post:
          url: "/{{uuid}}/message"
          name: "POST /mint-request (onchain)"
          gzip: true
          headers:
            "Content-Type": "application/json"
          json:
            text: hi
```

Just post `{"text": "hi"}` to `http://localhost:3000/{uuid}/message`.

title: Direct Client POST /agents/:agentId/set {character} crashes with Exit status 7 using Postgres
body:
**Describe the bug**

I get the following crash error when calling `POST /agents/:agentId/set {character}`

```
 ERR_PNPM_RECURSIVE_RUN_FIRST_FAIL  @elizaos/agent@0.1.8+build.1 start: `node --loader ts-node/esm src/index.ts "--isRoot"`
Exit status 7
```

This does not happen when I call `POST /agents/:agentId/set {character}` upon first starting Eliza. That works fine. At this point I am just creating the agent for the first time. I'm not loading the character via the filesystem.

This issue only occurs once the service has been running for some time and the agent is happily chatting on Telegram and posting on X, and then I make a call to update the character.

BTW, I'm running on postgres.

**To Reproduce**

- Start Eliza with the default character and using postgresql.
- Create/Start an agent via the Direct Client API with `POST /agents/:agentId/set {character}`
